ATTENTION! Limits of the regex approach:

printf("Two forward slashes // in a string");
printf("/* a comment in a string */");
printf("/* this is not");
printf("a multi-line");
printf("comment! */");

That being said...

// single line comment
code followed by a // comment

/* single line comment */
code followed by /* single line comment */
code with a nested /* single line comment */ and some more code
code with a nested /**/ (empty) comment
code with a nested /* comment with nested // forward slashes */ and some more code

/* multi-line
	comment */

code
/**
 * Javadoc multi-line
 *	comment
 */
code
////////////////////
// fancy comment  //
////////////////////
code
/*****************
 * fancy comment *
 ****************/ 
code
/************************* separators ***********************/
code
/************************************************************/
code
/* -------------------------------------------------------- */
code
/* thanks */
